# Lowercase copy

All user-facing text in this app is **lowercase only** — labels, buttons, titles, subtitles, errors, alerts, placeholders, tab names, and widget labels.

- Write strings in lowercase: `your habit has a heartbeat.` not `Your habit has a heartbeat.`
- Do not use `textTransform: 'uppercase'` on UI text.
- Locale-formatted dates should be lowercased before display (e.g. `july 2026`).
- External API error messages should be lowercased before showing to the user.
- Exceptions: email addresses, URLs, env var names, and user-entered values (habit name, pet name).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<Text>Welcome Back</Text>
options={{ title: 'Home' }}
textTransform: 'uppercase'

// ✅ GOOD
<Text>welcome back</Text>
options={{ title: 'home' }}
```
